   <body>
      <p>With the Adobe Sign package version v23, Adobe Sign has introduced Files as the new
         document storage type. You can configure the<uicontrol>Agreement Document Storage
            Type</uicontrol> custom setting in <uicontrol>Adobe Sign Settings</uicontrol> to define
         the document storage type. The supported document storage types are . If you leave this
         custom <uicontrol>Files and Attachments</uicontrol> setting blank, the system considers
            <uicontrol>Attachments </uicontrol>as the default value.</p>
